-- Man Arrested After Four Stabbed in Knife Attack on Bus Passengers in Japan
-- B y   Y u k i   Y a m a g u c h i
-- 2010-12-17T02:51:30Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-12-17/man-arrested-after-13-injured-in-knife-attack-on-passenger-bus-in-japan.html
Japanese police arrested a 27-year-
old man suspected of stabbing bus passengers near a station in
Ibaraki prefecture, north of Tokyo.  Thirteen people were injured in the attack at about 7:40
a.m. today, according to a local police spokesman reached by
telephone.   Four people were stabbed and others sustained injuries
while trying to avoid the attack, Kyodo News reported. None of
the injuries was serious, Kyodo said.   Most of the injured were local junior and senior high
school students, Kyodo said.   To contact the reporter on this story:
Yuki Yamaguchi in Tokyo at 
